title: A downed power line killed two people in the Orlando area.
dc:creator: Johnny Diaz

media:content.media:credit: Stephen M. Dowell/Orlando Sentinel, via Associated Press
media:content.media:description: The storm knocked down power lines across Florida, blacking out power for hundreds of thousands of customers. Linemen worked to repair lines on Spring Lake Road in Fruitland Park, Fla., on Thursday.
